This paper deals with learning algorithms for repeated auctions, which is a topic that falls under game theory (cs.GT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus on revenue optimization and regret bounds suggests that this paper also belongs to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the use of mathematical analysis and optimization techniques suggests that this paper may also belong to the sub-categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and economics (cs.EC).
